Reasoning: The paper describes a method for a robotic mobile manipulator to acquire kinematic models of objects through visual observation, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The method involves capturing depth imagery and using sparse feature tracking, motion segmentation, component pose estimation, and articulation learning, which are all techniques commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions inferring information from visual demonstrations, which suggests the use of machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the potential benefits of this method for human-robot interaction, which could fall under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
